metadata.window:
Product Manager (PM): Initially, we might only
need one PM to handle product vision, user
research, feature prioritization, and market
strategy. As the startup grows, we can consider
adding a Product Owner to focus on detailed
backlog management and sprint planning.
UX/UI Designer: A single designer with
experience in both user experience and user
interface design can handle the app's design
aspects, ensuring it's user-friendly and visually
appealing.Product TeamBuilding teams
AI/ML Engineer: CNN and computer vision particularly
those with experience in image recognition and multi
classifier. They can develop and refine the AI model for
food identification.
Data engineering team has for goal to set up the
environment of data for the AI team but also to create
the processes to extract data for example from
Instagram which has a lot of food pictures, sometimes
associated with description as well. They worked in
close relationship with Ai teams.

metadata.window:
KPIs 
User Retention Rate
Measure the percentage of users who
continue to use the app over time. High
retention rates suggest that users find
value in the app.
AI accuracy rate
The percentage of correctly
identified foods and accurately
calculated nutritional information.
Crucial for user trustDaily Active Users or Monthly Active
Users 
Indicates user engagement and the
app's growth trajectory.
Customer Satisfaction
User feedback through ratings and
reviews to gauge overall satisfaction
with the app
